      <profileDesc>
         <abstract>
            <p>The Wǝddāse Māryām is the short title of a famous office of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church, consisting of blessings and praise of the Mother of God and intercessions to her.
            </p>
            <p>In some manuscripts, the lection for Sunday is the first, in others the lection for Monday, but this difference does not constitute two textual traditions.</p>
         </abstract>
